16F628:
-- 2k words flash, hw USART

include print
include delay

-- hw usart debug
const serial_hw_baudrate = 19200
include serial_hardware

if defined(serial_sw_init) == true then
   -- use software usart interface
   alias debug_out is serial_sw_data
else
   -- use hardware usart interface
   alias debug_out is serial_hw_data
end if

procedure print(byte in str[]) is
    print_string(debug_out,str)
end procedure

procedure println(byte in str[]) is
   debug_out = "\r"
   debug_out = "\n"
   print(str)
end procedure

-- analog_off()
enable_digital_io() -- make all pins digital I/O

16F88:
;
; for 16F88
;
-- initJALCode

include print
include delay

const serial_hw_baudrate = 19200
include serial_hardware

if defined(serial_sw_init) == true then
   -- use software usart interface
   alias debug_out is serial_sw_data
else
   -- use hardware usart interface
   alias debug_out is serial_hw_data
end if

procedure print(byte in str[]) is
    print_string(debug_out,str)
end procedure

procedure println(byte in str[]) is
   debug_out = "\r"
   debug_out = "\n"
   print(str)
end procedure

-- initialize PIC
-- set OSCCON if needed
if target_clock == 4_000_000  then
   OSCCON = 108 -- 4 mhz for 16F88
end if
if target_clock == 8_000_000  then
   OSCCON = 124 -- 8 mhz for 16F88
end if

analog_off()
enable_digital_io() -- make all pins digital I/O

if defined(serial_hw_init) == true then
   serial_hw_init()
end if

delay_1ms(300)
println("Start program ")
if target_clock == 4_000_000  then
  print("4 MHz")
end if
if target_clock == 8_000_000  then
  print("8 MHz")
end if
println("\r\n")
